\chapter{Margin Figures}

These are widely used in the tufte-book class. You can use it as you wish.



\begin{verbatim}
\begin{marginfigure}[15cm]
  \includegraphics[width=1.0\textwidth]{../beta/che.jpg}
  \caption{\captionlorem}
\end{marginfigure}

\\\\[a+b\\\\]
\lorem
\end{verbatim}


\begin{marginfigure}

  \\[a+b\\] 
  
  \includegraphics[width=1.0\textwidth]{../beta/che.jpg}
  
  \caption*{\captionlorem }
 
\end{marginfigure}

\lorem \\(a+b\\)



